# Chat thread surfaces

- **`ChatThread.tsx`** and **`GroupChatThread.tsx`** must **not** duplicate large blocks of behaviour. Prefer:
  - **Shared hooks** in `client/src/chat/` or `client/src/hooks/` (keyboard, composer, scroll-to-latest, media preview, outbox).
  - **Shared presentational** pieces beside existing `MessageBubble`, `ChatHeader`, etc.
- **New messaging features** (reactions, attachments, typing, media pipeline): implement once in **`client/src/chat/`**, wire from both pages.
- **API paths** pair with **`backend/blueprints/group_chat.py`** and **`dm_chats`** / **`MYSQL_AND_FIRESTORE.md`** — confirm route inventory after backend changes (`python scripts/generate_route_inventory.py`).
- See **`docs/MONOLITH_REDUCTION_ROADMAP.md`** § Chat UI kernel and **`AGENTS.md`** for AI/voice (Steve) invariants if the change touches summaries or usage.

## Inverted chat list (open-at-bottom invariant)

- The chat message list is rendered with **`flex-direction: column-reverse`** on the scroll container (see `ChatThread.tsx`, `GroupChatThread.tsx`, `ChatThreadShell.tsx`). `scrollTop = 0` IS the visual bottom. The newest message is at the bottom from the first paint frame — there is **no JS pin on open**, no reveal timer, no `opacity: 0` / `visibility: hidden` gate, no `fastOpen` bypass.
- The DOM child order under the column-reverse container is reversed visually: **first DOM child = visual bottom**, last DOM child = visual top. The page wires this as: `<ChatVirtualMessageList />` first (newest at visual bottom of the stack), then the load-older spinner / button, then the empty state. Inside `ChatVirtualMessageList`, messages stay in natural (oldest → newest) order.
- Scroll helpers in `client/src/chat/scrollPin.ts` use inverted semantics: `isInvertedAtBottom(el)`, `pinInvertedToBottom(el)`, `smoothPinInvertedToBottom(el)`, `distanceFromInvertedBottom(el)`, `distanceFromInvertedTop(el)`. Do not reintroduce `scrollTop = scrollHeight - clientHeight` against the chat list — that is the non-inverted convention and will fight the layout.
- **Load-older must not adjust `scrollTop`.** Column-reverse anchors layout at the visual bottom, so prepending older messages preserves the user's visual position automatically. Do **not** capture `scrollHeight` before the prepend and then set `el.scrollTop = newHeight - prevHeight` in a `requestAnimationFrame` — that is the non-inverted restore formula and will visibly jump the view. Just prepend the older rows into state and return.
- **`useChatThreadScroll`** keeps only: `userHasScrolledRef`, `pendingNewCount`, `showScrollDown`, `ensurePinnedToBottom` / `scrollToBottomSmooth` (post-send / FAB tap helpers), `notifyMessagesSettled` (no-op unless the user is at bottom, then clears pending count). No `initialPinActiveRef`, `programmaticScrollRef`, `listRevealReady`, `listOpening`, `revealTimer`, or `pinUnlockTimer`. Do not reintroduce them.
- Thread pages must still funnel **`notifyMessagesSettled`** through a ref (`notifyMessagesSettledRef.current(gen)`) inside fetch/poll callbacks, and must **not** include `notifyMessagesSettled` in `useEffect` dependency arrays.
- **Cache-first hydrate** must `mergeHydratedMessages` / preserve optimistic rows — never `setMessages(processed)` alone when outbox or in-flight sends may exist.
- After cache paint, network refresh may run in the background; avoid duplicate `refreshBadges()` when the server payload is unchanged.
- Composer + keyboard inset is `padding-bottom` on the inverted container. Keyboard motion is JS-smoothed via `useSmoothedPx` and updates per RAF tick. **Idle** inset changes (post-paint composer remeasure, late safe-area sync, active-use chrome growth like mention dropdown or upload banner) are CSS-transitioned via `chat-list-idle-smooth` (250ms `cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1)`), **gated by `insetMotionIdle` from `useChatComposerChrome`** so the transition is suppressed whenever the keyboard is open or animating (no double-easing, no padding lag behind composer lift). Both `ChatThread.tsx` and `GroupChatThread.tsx` must apply the `chat-list-idle-smooth` class on their inline list element when `insetMotionIdle` is true; do not gate it on anything else (no `snapListInset` open-window special case, no fastOpen).
- **Reactions are per-message fields, not a sibling state map.** Both `ChatThread.tsx` and `GroupChatThread.tsx` read `msg.reaction` directly. Do not introduce a `useState<Record<number, string>>({})` for reactions — it splits the source of truth and causes reactions to pop in one frame after the bubble paints. Cache reads, network reconciles, and optimistic writes must all update the reaction field on the message row itself.

## First-paint parity (DM ↔ group)

- Neither thread page may render a full-screen "Loading..." placeholder that swaps to the chat UI once data resolves. The chat shell renders unconditionally; any "still loading" state shows as an inline spinner inside the inverted message list. Do not reintroduce an `if (loading && !group) return <LoadingScreen />` early return in `GroupChatThread.tsx`.
- The header chrome (group title / DM peer display name + avatar) must be seedable from a **synchronous** device cache read at component mount — async IndexedDB lookups alone cause the header to flash in late. Use `useState(() => readDeviceCache(...))` (and re-seed inside the `useLayoutEffect` that resets state on `group_id` / peer-username change). Mirror server group/peer payloads back to the same device cache key after each network refresh.
- Inset state used by the inverted list (`safeBottomPx`, composer height) must be present on the first paint frame. `useChatComposerChrome` and `useFixedComposerKeyboard` seed `safeBottomPx` synchronously from `--sab-px` and use `useLayoutEffect` for subsequent syncs. Textarea auto-height (`adjustTextareaHeight`) is committed in a `useLayoutEffect`, never a post-paint `useEffect` — otherwise the resulting `listPaddingBottom` change visibly shifts the message list upward by a few pixels.
- **Composer height cache is per-surface.** `useChatComposerChrome` keys its module-level cache and the matching `--chat-composer-height-${surface}` CSS var by `surfaceKey: 'dm' | 'group'`. Both `ChatThread.tsx` (`surfaceKey: 'dm'`) and `GroupChatThread.tsx` (`surfaceKey: 'group'`) must pass it through `useChatThreadChrome`. The two cards differ by 1–4px even at idle (different gap classes, mention dropdown / upload banner slot on group), so a shared cache caused cross-surface seeding and visible post-paint drift on the inverted list. Do not collapse back to a single global cache.
- Do not call `setLoading(true)` inside the polling / `loadMessages` paths when a device cache has already painted the thread; the inline spinner is for cold opens only.
- **`MessageImage` reserves bubble height before decode.** Chat bubble images use `aspect-ratio` + `max-height: 320px` on the wrapper, seeded from a session cache (`messageImageAspect.ts`) or a portrait default (3:4). A `useLayoutEffect` dimension probe runs when the URL is not cached so browser-cache hits often resolve before paint. Do not revert to inline-only `<img max-height>` without a reserved box — late image decode on the newest row shifts the inverted list.
